title: Grateful Dead Live at Kiel Auditorium on 1981-07-08
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi CR-5A > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > CD-Wave (24bit output) > TLH > FLAC 2448 tagged. Transferred by Andrew F. 08/2015
description:
Set 1

Mississippi Half Step-> Feel Like A Stranger, Peggy-O-> Little Red Rooster, Althea, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Don't Ease Me In, Minglewood Blues, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Franklin's Tower-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: It has been a long time coming Thank you to the folks who filled this gap in our collections. Very nice China/Rider and Scarlet/Fire. Lots of Phil bombs throughout the show. If I had been in attendance no doubt I would have left with a Cheshire Cat grin.
Thanks so much for my FIRST SHOW WOW only a 1 million per cent better sound than the old hot dog stand tape, thanks so much!
